race.comment: After the scratchings of two of the strongly fancied runner THE MOUNT (4) look very hard to beat. Resumed from a good break at Werribee with a fast finishing third. Same class here and similar trip. Will strip fitter and is a second-up winner. Looks tough to stop. JUDGE KELLIE (7) was a winner two back then raced on pace at Nhill but was swamped late. Will give a sight again in this small field. EMERALD COURT (9) tried to lead throughout here last time and was nabbed right on the line. Has a low draw and a light weight with the claim and should take catching. IN THE SUN (10) was well off best over the border last time but previous form good for this and worth noting was a course and distance winner only other try.
